message.content: <OUTPUT_TEXT>To appraise and inventory real and personal property for estate planning, you need to: 1) Identify all assets, including real estate, personal property, bank accounts, investments, and any other valuables. 2) Obtain professional appraisals for real estate and valuable personal property to determine fair market value. 3) Compile a detailed inventory list, including descriptions, values, and ownership details. 4) Document any debts or liabilities associated with the assets. 5) Ensure all information is up-to-date and accurately reflects the current status of the assets for effective estate planning.</OUTPUT_TEXT>
